cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper discusses automated facial expression recognition (AFER) and automated pain detection (APD) using deep learning methods, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on clinical applications suggests a potential fit for the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the use of databases for training and testing the models aligns with the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the mention of strategies and considerations in developing a FACS-based pain detection framework suggests a potential fit for the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
